turn.2: WIIH-CD WIIH-CD, virtual channel 17 (VHF digital channel 8), is a low-powered, Class A getTV-affiliated television station licensed to Indianapolis, Indiana, United States.
turn.3: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.4: Owned by Circle City Broadcasting, it is a sister station to Circle City's duopoly of Indianapolis-licensed CW affiliate WISH-TV (channel 8) and Marion-licensed MyNetworkTV affiliate WNDY-TV (channel 23).
turn.5: Do they have the same frequency as each other?
turn.6: The three stations share studios on North Meridian Street (at the north end of the Television Row section) on the near north side of Indianapolis and transmitter facilities on Walnut Drive in the Augusta section of the city's northwest side (near Meridian Hills).
turn.7: Do they have any other affiliations?
turn.8: Even though WIIH-CD broadcasts a digital signal of its own, its broadcast radius is limited to the immediate Indianapolis area.
turn.9: Is it the same for WMYD?
turn.10: It is therefore simulcast on WISH-TV's second digital subchannel (VHF channel 9.2 or virtual channel 8.2 via PSIP) in order to reach the entire market.
turn.11: When did the station first air?
turn.12: The station first signed on the air on January 29, 1988 as W11BV, broadcasting on VHF channel 11.
